   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Extreme overloading can cause permanent bending or immediate
failure of the forks. Using forks of less capacity than the load or
lift truck when lifting loads and using forks in a manner for which
they were not designed are some common causes of overloading.</p>
